Consensus sequences

This section shows the consensus sequences assembled from the sequencing reads. Based on the data shown here, the analyst should select one of more consensus sequences as a reference for taxonomic identification of the sample.

It is likely that not all sequences shown here match the sample organism. Erroneous sequences often result from sample contamination or from sequencing/assembly artefacts. It is the responsibility of the analyst to select the most appropriate sequence(s) for taxonomic identification based on the evidence shown. Furthermore, the results shown here cannot be used to make a confident assessment of the sample taxonomy. Taxonomic identity should be determined by downstream analysis.

Definitions of flags used in this analysis

Flags are discrete indicators of consensus sequence quality. Definitions of each flag and their possible values are listed below.

FLAG NAME DEFINITION GREEN ORANGE RED GREY
QC_FLAG Number of starting raw reads and quality filtered reads recovered for each sample >= 2500 starting reads & >= 200 quality filtered reads < 2500 starting reads & >= 200 quality filtered reads < 2500 starting reads & < 200 quality filtered reads NA
30X COVERAGE FLAG The percentage of bases that attained at least 30X sequence coverage when mapping back to the consensus match (ie qseq) > 90% 75-90% < 75% The consensus returned no blast hits
TARGET ORGANISM FLAG Flag based on whether the consensus matched to the target organism(s) by blast homology search and the % blast identity recovered Target organism detected and blast identity > 90% Target organism was detected and blast identity < 90% Target organism not detected The consensus returned no blast hits
TARGET SIZE FLAG Length of the consensus match (ie qseq) relative to the expected target_size within ±20% ±20%-±40% outside the range of ±40% The consensus returned no blast hits
MAPPED READ COUNT FLAG Number of reads mapping back to the consensus match (ie qseq) >= 1000 200-1000 < 200 The consensus returned no blast hits
MEAN COVERAGE FLAG Mean read coverage of each base when mapping back to the consensus match (ie qseq) >= 500 100-500 < 100 The consensus returned no blast hits
READ LENGTH FLAG Number of mapped reads whose lengths are at least 90% of the consensus match length >=200 50-200 < 50 The consensus returned no blast hits
MEAN MQ FLAG Average mapping quality of reads mapping to the consensus match >= 30 10-30 < 10 The consensus returned no blast hits
